    <b><u>Research</u></b> 
<p> My research interests are in Machine Learning, Artificial
  Intellgence, and Data Mining. My current work focuses on
  computational and statistical aspects of over-parameterized models
  including deep learning and generative models. I am also interested
  in sequential decision making problems. <br><br>

  I also work on applications of machine learning and data sciences in
complex real world learning problems including problems in Climate
Sciences, Ecology and Environmental Sciences, Recommendation Systems,
and Finance, among others.
</p>
<p>Here is a list of our <a href="publications.html">Publications</a>.
</p>

<p> <b> Prospective Students: </b> We are looking for strong MS and PhD
students, both in core Machine Learning (ML) and application of ML to
scientific problems. Please look through
our <a href="research.html">Research</a> and
recent <a href="publications.html">Publications</a> to get a sense of
our work. <br><br>

<b> Note:</b> Given the high volume of emails, I am unable to respond to individual emails from prospective students. If you are interested in working with our group (as MS or PhD student), please select/mention my name in your graduate application to UIUC, then your application will be routed to me. <br><br>

